earning practical guidance is provided helping teachers develop skills and practices focused on the learning process within their classrooms. In the fi nal chapter information is given about the way teachers can professionalize further in their teaching career. Addresses innovative teaching methods and strategies. Includes a section of practical examples and exercises in the end of each chapter. Written by one of the top experts in chemistry education. Jan Apotheker taught chemistry for 25 years at the Praedinius Gymnasium, Groningen. In 1998 he became a lecturer in chemistry education at the University of Groningen, retired in 2016. He is currently chair of the Committee on Chemistry Education of the IUPAC.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aChemistry teachersxTraining of. 0aChemistryxStudy and teaching (Secondary) 7aSCIENCE / Chemistry / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE  DG 2019 Englishz978311061685908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chem., Mat.Sc, Geosc 2019 Englishz978311061064208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry,  Materials Sc, Geosc 2019z9783110606461oZDB-23-DPC0 cEPUBz97831105697800 cprintz978311056961240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311056962940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110569629423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110569629.jpg  a978-3-11-061064-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chem., Mat.Sc, Geosc 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK